statements.sql:
select `customers`.`name`, sum((invoice_products.price * invoice_products.quantity) - invoice_products.discount) as price, sum((invoice_payments.amount)) as pay_price, (SELECT SUM((price * quantity - discount) * (taxes.rate / 100)) FROM invoice_products
LEFT JOIN taxes ON FIND_IN_SET(taxes.id, invoice_products.tax) > 0
WHERE invoice_products.invoice_id = invoices.id) as total_tax, (SELECT SUM(credit_notes.amount) FROM credit_notes
WHERE credit_notes.invoice = invoices.id) as credit_price from `invoices` left join `customers` on `customers`.`id` = `invoices`.`customer_id` left join `invoice_payments` on `invoice_payments`.`invoice_id` = `invoices`.`id` left join `invoice_products` on `invoice_products`.`invoice_id` = `invoices`.`id` where `invoices`.`created_by` = 2 and `invoices`.`issue_date` >= '2024-01-01' and `invoices`.`issue_date` <= '2024-08-01' group by `invoices`.`invoice_id`

select `customers`.`name`, (invoices.invoice_id) as invoice, sum((invoice_products.price * invoice_products.quantity) - invoice_products.discount) as price, sum((invoice_payments.amount)) as pay_price, (SELECT SUM((price * quantity - discount) * (taxes.rate / 100)) FROM invoice_products
LEFT JOIN taxes ON FIND_IN_SET(taxes.id, invoice_products.tax) > 0
WHERE invoice_products.invoice_id = invoices.id) as total_tax, invoices.issue_date as issue_date, invoices.status as status from `invoices` left join `customers` on `customers`.`id` = `invoices`.`customer_id` left join `invoice_payments` on `invoice_payments`.`invoice_id` = `invoices`.`id` left join `invoice_products` on `invoice_products`.`invoice_id` = `invoices`.`id` where `invoices`.`created_by` = 2 and `invoices`.`issue_date` >= '2024-01-01' and `invoices`.`issue_date` <= '2024-08-01' group by `invoices`.`invoice_id`

select `customers`.`name`, null as invoice, (credit_notes.amount) as price, 0 as pay_price, 0 as total_tax, credit_notes.date as issue_date, 5 as status from `credit_notes` left join `customers` on `customers`.`id` = `credit_notes`.`customer` left join `invoice_products` on `invoice_products`.`invoice_id` = `credit_notes`.`invoice` left join `invoices` on `invoices`.`id` = `credit_notes`.`invoice` where `invoices`.`created_by` = 2 and `credit_notes`.`date` >= '2024-01-01' and `credit_notes`.`date` <= '2024-08-01' group by `credit_notes`.`id`

select `customers`.`name`, (invoices.invoice_id) as invoice, sum(invoice_products.price) as price, (invoice_products.quantity) as quantity, (product_services.name) as product_name, invoices.issue_date as issue_date, invoices.status as status from `invoices` left join `customers` on `customers`.`id` = `invoices`.`customer_id` left join `invoice_products` on `invoice_products`.`invoice_id` = `invoices`.`id` left join `product_services` on `product_services`.`id` = `invoice_products`.`product_id` where `invoices`.`created_by` = 2 and `invoices`.`issue_date` >= '2024-01-01' and `invoices`.`issue_date` <= '2024-08-01' group by `invoices`.`invoice_id`, `product_services`.`name`

select `customers`.`name`, null as invoice, (credit_notes.id) as invoices, (credit_notes.amount) as price, (product_services.name) as product_name, credit_notes.date as issue_date, 5 as status from `credit_notes` left join `customers` on `customers`.`id` = `credit_notes`.`customer` left join `invoice_products` on `invoice_products`.`invoice_id` = `credit_notes`.`invoice` left join `product_services` on `product_services`.`id` = `invoice_products`.`product_id` left join `invoices` on `invoices`.`id` = `credit_notes`.`invoice` where `invoices`.`created_by` = 2 and `credit_notes`.`date` >= '2024-01-01' and `credit_notes`.`date` <= '2024-08-01' group by `credit_notes`.`id`, `product_services`.`name`

select `customers`.`name`, `invoices`.`due_date` as `due_date`, `invoices`.`status` as `status`, `invoices`.`invoice_id` as `invoice_id`, sum((invoice_products.price * invoice_products.quantity) - invoice_products.discount) as price, sum((invoice_payments.amount)) as pay_price, (SELECT SUM((price * quantity - discount) * (taxes.rate / 100)) FROM invoice_products
LEFT JOIN taxes ON FIND_IN_SET(taxes.id, invoice_products.tax) > 0
WHERE invoice_products.invoice_id = invoices.id) as total_tax, (SELECT SUM(credit_notes.amount) FROM credit_notes
WHERE credit_notes.invoice = invoices.id) as credit_price from `invoices` left join `customers` on `customers`.`id` = `invoices`.`customer_id` left join `invoice_payments` on `invoice_payments`.`invoice_id` = `invoices`.`id` left join `invoice_products` on `invoice_products`.`invoice_id` = `invoices`.`id` where `invoices`.`created_by` = 2 and `invoices`.`issue_date` >= '2024-01-01' and `invoices`.`issue_date` <= '2024-08-01' group by `invoices`.`invoice_id`

select `permissions`.*, `model_has_permissions`.`model_id` as `pivot_model_id`, `model_has_permissions`.`permission_id` as `pivot_permission_id`, `model_has_permissions`.`model_type` as `pivot_model_type` from `permissions` inner join `model_has_permissions` on `permissions`.`id` = `model_has_permissions`.`permission_id` where `model_has_permissions`.`model_id` = 2 and `model_has_permissions`.`model_type` = 'App\Models\User'

select `roles`.*, `model_has_roles`.`model_id` as `pivot_model_id`, `model_has_roles`.`role_id` as `pivot_role_id`, `model_has_roles`.`model_type` as `pivot_model_type` from `roles` inner join `model_has_roles` on `roles`.`id` = `model_has_roles`.`role_id` where `model_has_roles`.`model_id` in (2) and `model_has_roles`.`model_type` = 'App\Models\User'
